      <section id="id17590487">
        <title>Chapter 5</title>
        <para id="id11366781">The kind shoemaker and his kind wife made some new clothes for the little elves.</para>
        <para id="id10351973">That night they left the new clothes with the leather.</para>
        <para id="id10680233">When the clock struck twelve, the three little elves came in to stitch the shoes.</para>
        <para id="id9987208">They saw the beautiful clothes and put them on.</para>
        <para id="id15517818">They rapped and tapped until all the shoes were made. Then they ran away and were never seen again.</para>
        <para id="id11522259">The shoemaker and his wife were rich.</para>
        <para id="id9466960">They made many pairs of shoes and sold them. They lived happily ever after.</para>
